  "texts": [
    "First, as mentioned above, we maintained equal sample sizes by saving the top 100 solutions from the final population for both GA and RL, while the random algorithm also generated 100 random solutions.",
    "This allowed for an equitable comparison of the evaluated inputs.",
    "All algorithms were tested within the same input space and under identical conditions, ensuring that any performance differences were due to the characteristics of the algorithms rather than external factors.",
    "Consistency in fitness evaluation was maintained, as the same metrics-such as execution time and diversity-were applied uniformly across all algorithms.",
    "Additionally, all algorithms, including the random one, were run multiple times, selecting the best results from these trials."
